  "prompt": "Does IIM Indore select 1 year dropouts for IPM?",
  "response": "The Indian Institute of Management (IIM) Indore offers the Integrated Programme in Management (IPM), which is designed for students after their 10+2 education. While there is no official restriction against admitting candidates who have taken a one-year drop, the admission process and eligibility criteria primarily focus on academic performance, entrance exam scores, and overall profile.\n\nIf you have taken a one-year gap but meet the eligibility criteria and perform well in the required entrance exams (like the IPMAT for IPM), you could be considered for admission. It\u2019s best to check directly with IIM Indore\u2019s official admissions guidelines or contact their admissions office for the most accurate and detailed information regarding your specific situation.",
